  { '@type': 'Question', name: 'Do elderberry gummies actually work for adults?', acceptedAnswer: { '@type': 'Answer', text: 'A 2019 meta-analysis in Complementary Therapies in Medicine analyzed four randomized controlled trials and found that elderberry supplementation significantly reduced the duration and severity of upper respiratory infections compared to placebo. Adults who took elderberry experienced colds that were on average 2 days shorter with measurably reduced symptom severity. The active compounds in elderberry — anthocyanins and flavonoids — appear to work by blocking viral entry into cells and stimulating cytokine production to enhance immune response. However, elderberry is most effective when taken at the onset of symptoms rather than as a preventive supplement, and should complement (not replace) medical care for serious infections.' } },
  { '@type': 'Question', name: 'How much elderberry should adults take daily?', acceptedAnswer: { '@type': 'Answer', text: 'For general immune support, most elderberry supplements provide 100-200mg of concentrated sambucus extract per serving, taken once daily. During active cold or flu symptoms, some protocols recommend increasing to 2-4 servings daily for 3-5 days (under healthcare provider guidance). The equivalent dose in raw elderberry is approximately 500-1,000mg, but concentrated extracts standardized to anthocyanin content are more consistent and effective than raw berry preparations. Always follow the specific product label, as extract concentrations vary significantly between brands. Do not exceed the recommended dose — more is not necessarily better with elderberry.' } },
