  { '@type': 'Question', name: 'Are elderberry gummies safe for adults with autoimmune conditions?', acceptedAnswer: { '@type': 'Answer', text: 'This requires caution and medical consultation. Elderberry stimulates the innate immune system by increasing cytokine production (IL-1, IL-6, TNF-alpha). For individuals with autoimmune conditions where the immune system is already overactive (rheumatoid arthritis, lupus, multiple sclerosis, Crohn\'s disease), additional immune stimulation is theoretically undesirable and could exacerbate symptoms. There is no direct clinical evidence showing elderberry worsening autoimmune conditions, but the theoretical mechanism of immune overstimulation warrants caution. Always consult your rheumatologist or immunologist before taking elderberry or any immune-stimulating supplement if you have an autoimmune diagnosis.' } },
