      <div class="info-card"><div class="info-card-ico"><Icon name="zap" size={22} /></div><strong>Cytokine Activation</strong><p>Elderberry increases production of IL-1 beta, IL-6, and TNF-alpha — inflammatory cytokines that recruit and activate immune cells to fight active infections. This amplifies the body's natural immune response during the critical first 48-72 hours of illness.</p></div>
      <div class="info-card"><div class="info-card-ico"><Icon name="leaf" size={22} /></div><strong>Antioxidant Protection</strong><p>Anthocyanins in elderberry are potent antioxidants that neutralize free radicals generated during immune response. This protects healthy tissues from collateral oxidative damage while the immune system fights infection.</p></div>
