    </div>

    <div class="callout">
      <p>A randomized, double-blind, placebo-controlled trial published in <em>Nutrients</em> found that <strong>elderberry supplementation reduced cold duration by 33% and symptom severity by 36%</strong> in air travelers — a population with elevated infection risk due to cabin air recirculation and close-proximity seating. The study used standardized elderberry extract equivalent to the doses found in premium adult elderberry gummies.</p>
